{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fc12fb02-a83d-402e-9676-002fafc9dd5c","content":"No files found in the working directory. Since there's no existing code, here's exactly how to convert your page:\n\n### 1. Add `x:DataType` to enable compiled bindings\n\nIn your `SettingsPage.xaml`, add the `xmlns:vm` namespace pointing to your ViewModel and set `x:DataType` on the `ContentPage`:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" FontSize=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n\n        <Entry Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" Placeholder=\"Theme\" />\n\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n\n        <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"10\" Maximum=\"36\" Increment=\"2\" />\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe **only change** vs. your current file is adding the `xmlns:vm` namespace and `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"`. All existing `{Binding ...}` expressions stay the same — the compiler now resolves them against `SettingsViewModel` at build time.\n\n### 2. Catch binding errors at build time\n\nAdd this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Emit warnings for bindings that can't be compiled -->\n  <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nWith `x:DataType` set and strict compilation enabled:\n\n- **Typos** like `{Binding Themee}` become **build errors**, not silent runtime failures.\n- **Type mismatches** (e.g., binding `FontSize` (int) to a property expecting a string without a converter) are flagged.\n- If you need to **opt out** for a specific subtree (e.g., a dynamically-typed area), set `x:DataType=\"{x:Null}\"` on that element.\n\n### 3. Code-behind (no changes needed)\n\nYour existing code-behind just needs to set `BindingContext` as before:\n\n```csharp\npublic SettingsPage(SettingsViewModel vm)\n{\n    InitializeComponent();\n    BindingContext = vm;\n}\n```\n\n**Summary:** Add `x:DataType` → bindings compile to direct property access (faster, type-safe). Enable `MauiStrictXamlCompilation` → mismatched or misspelled bindings fail the build instead of silently breaking at runtime.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2ff7faed-4be1-472d-a432-10ba1431dcc6","outputTokens":698,"requestId":"1015:189FE3:14E0761:177607A:69FD33CA"},"id":"5eee60cd-4b21-441a-aa71-5179ea0b4f84","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:52:42.869Z","parentId":"79a051bd-9576-4a38-8621-d8134eb92f96"}
